reviews.author: Bill Hogan
reviews.text: Great place to see the ocean or watch the sun go down.  Apparently, the island off in the distance used to be a prison.  The alcatraz of Peru.  I was told itbis uninhabited now

reviews.author: Arturo Ñaupa
reviews.text: Nice to hace a walkstreet and to take pictures of the sunset.

reviews.author: Enrique Rubinos
reviews.text:
Excellent view of the ocean on a clear day
To the south you can get a glimse of the Regatas Nautical Club, to the North you can get to see La Punta at Callao ( a peninsula surrounded by the Pacific Ocean) and the San Lorenzo Island which protects the port of Callao.

reviews.author: Rio Charis
reviews.text: Nice place. For sunset and great view of the herrafira beach and other beaches

reviews.author: David Rodriguez
reviews.text: Not as good as the ones in miraflores but a still a very good view for strolls along the coast.

reviews.author: David Stanley
reviews.text: The Mirador Catalina Recavarren in the Barranco district of Lima, Perú, offers views of Playa Barranco and the high bluffs running along the Pacific coast. In one photo a girl celebrates her quinceañera (15th birthday) at the Mirador.

reviews.author: Bruno Rodríguez Armesto
reviews.text: We sat for a while listening to the waves and an old man playing songs on his guitar. It’s quite peaceful.

reviews.author: A Cortez
reviews.text: Great spot in Barranco to view the ocean. Had the pleasure of listening to local musician during our visit.

reviews.author: Carlos Eduardo
reviews.text: Nice view. Not that so special.

reviews.author: Josue qh
reviews.text: Sunset

reviews.author: Keith Moore
reviews.text: This is a nice spot to take some panoramic photos of the Lima coastline.  There are public bathrooms on the walk to the lookout point, and there is a crossing to the beach if you are interested, although the beach is not great here.

reviews.author: Shreya Gupta
reviews.text:
- Good place with great views
- I don’t think they have a proper beach or clean water that you can go into it but they have parks by the water. So, it’s a good area to visit in the evening by the sunset.
- They have good restaurants too.

reviews.author: Jean-Yves Bourdon
reviews.text: Nice view, good place for pictures, it is free to visit

reviews.author: Bouchedid Josias
reviews.text: Nice view when it's sunny, quite average when it's grey.

reviews.author: Joel Espino
reviews.text: It's an excellent vantage point for enjoying a panoramic view of the beach. It has a relaxed, bohemian atmosphere, surrounded by urban art, trees, and street music, giving it a very special feel. It's ideal for strolling, taking photos at sunset, or simply sitting and admiring the scenery.

name: Mirador Arturo Polanco
address: Ml, Mal. Paúl Harris 207, Barranco 15063, Peru

reviews.author: Yu Jiang
reviews.text: good view but need be careful the security

reviews.author: Danny Pelizzon
reviews.text: Nice view over the sea.

reviews.author: noland Sims Jr
reviews.text: The views are breathtaking.

reviews.author: Sofia Vovk
reviews.text: The view is impressive. From there, you can clearly see the ocean and the entire Miraflores area. The place seems very peaceful, with lots of people walking or enjoying the ocean view. The entire area is very green, and the park looks well-maintained.

reviews.author: Alex Orellana
reviews.text: The place is new, there's flora, and you can get around by bike or on foot. It's a great place to spend some quality time.

reviews.author: Paul
reviews.text: While walking from the bridge of sighs towards the playa we stopped here for refreshments with a vista. Excelente!  Pisco sour, cerveza, and ceviche. All were wonderful.  Great location. Friendly service, clean bathrooms, and plenty of tables with a view to the playa de barranca.

reviews.author: Joelle Suarez
reviews.text: The food was pretty good. I tried anticucho for the first time and then later had ceviche. I probably wouldn't eat here again because I didn't feel it was that great. Personally I did not enjoy the service here, I found the staff to be rather inattentive and somewhat rude. The atmosphere is probably nicer during the way when you can see the vibrant trees and ocean off in the distant, but I came at night so it wasn't as nice as I'd hope.

reviews.author: Juliette AG
reviews.text: This seafood restaurant in Barranco, Lima, blends the charm of the bohemian district with exceptional Peruvian cuisine. Set in a vibrant neighborhood known for its art and culture, the restaurant offers a cozy, stylish atmosphere that reflects the area's creative spirit. The menu features fresh, locally sourced seafood, and Peruvian traditional dishes. Each dish is crafted with care, offering a true taste of Peru’s coastal heritage. With warm, attentive service and a relaxed vibe, it's an ideal spot to enjoy a delicious meal after exploring the colorful streets of Barranco.

reviews.author: Kyle Cournoyer
reviews.text: Really scenic spot in Barranco. Upstairs has a great view of the plaza and food was great! The chaufa was exactly what we needed after so much walking.

reviews.author: Robert Palmay
reviews.text: Waited 2 hours and our food never came, after asking what was happening they managed to get 2/5 plates on the table but the food wasn’t very good anyway (maybe because they threw it together quickly). This is probably the only 4 and under rating I’ve ever given, they didn’t seem to care when we brought our concerns to their attention so I wanted to make sure I posted this. There is a restaurant next door and saw those customers leaving happy, give them a try…

reviews.author: Johan Björefeldt
reviews.text: Nice viewpoint in south Barranco overlooking the beach line to north and south. The wall is covered in graffiti, which you may or may not consider adds to the atmosphere of the place.

reviews.author: Tim Chu
reviews.text: Semi public space with the entry at the end of the street. This view point may be closed depending on the private community near by. It offers unobstructed view of the Pacific Ocean, is free to access, and just a short walk from the Barranco main plaza. It's also very quiet and only visited by locals, not a single tourist in sight.

reviews.author: Schern
reviews.text: Pretty!

reviews.author: Jorge Gonzales M
reviews.text: Me relago

reviews.author: Linda Bejarano M
reviews.text: Beautiful!

reviews.author: SPICY
reviews.text: This bridge itself is pretty standard - about 40 feet long with no major views to speak of. But that's not what makes it special. The real treasure is the shops surrounding it, filled with unique art designs, cool jackets, t-shirts, and bags. It's evolved beyond just a marketplace - it's now a hub for creative expression. While the restaurants nearby are okay, they're not the main draw. The real highlight is the eclectic mix of art and shopping that makes this area worth exploring.

reviews.author: Desiree McConnell
reviews.text: At the Bridge of Sighs, we lucked out-the garúa had faded, leaving us with clear blue skies and a warm breeze. According to legend, if you hold your breath while walking across the bridge, your wish will be granted; and if you cross it with your lover, you are said to be blessed with eternal love. The surrounding area is delightful, with a cute park, vibrant murals, and intriguing street art that make it a perfect spot to wander and explore. Lovely area to walk around and explore or take your pup out to enjoy.

reviews.author: Me Lizzy
reviews.text: This is a beautiful tourist attraction in Barranco, Lima, Peru. Don't believe the legend that if you hold the hand of the one you love and cross the bridge while holding your breath, if you make it to the other side you will be together forever... total and utter lie 🤣🤣 Other than that there is a beautiful spot, art, food, and more to see and or eat. It also  leads down to the beach.

reviews.author: Frank Linskens
reviews.text: It’s nice area but unfortunately not as nice as I expected. Church is not lighted and that’s a pity. Would make pictures much more beautiful. Murals are nice.

reviews.author: t g
reviews.text: Great lil artsy area and the vendors there are nice and not pushy. Would have loved to visited in the evening when the bars were open as I think there’s music then.

reviews.author: Karlo Gutiérrez
reviews.text: On the outside they keep it very well cared for. Unfortunately I think it is not used as a museum and to be able to appreciate something from the time. Very few people know the place. But I hope they continue to maintain it as well as now.

reviews.author: Jose miguel Santamaria Relaiza
reviews.text: Interesting, it is on a very quiet and striking street.
